        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "improve: simplify PR context and evidence",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe PR template and external-contributor body gate were still tied to a rigid real-behavior-proof form. That made readable PRs harder to write and conflated two separate concerns: author-provided PR context versus ClawSweeper's stronger proof-sufficiency review.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nReplace the field-level proof form with authored `What Problem This Solves` and `Evidence` sections, and make Barnacle manage only the missing-context label `triage: needs-pr-context`. OpenClaw no longer emits or clears ClawSweeper-owned proof labels such as `proof: supplied`, `proof: sufficient`, or `proof: override`.\n\nCompanion ClawSweeper draft: https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/pull/319\n\n## User Impact\n\nAuthors can write concise PRs that explain intent, design, impact, and the most useful validation evidence. Reviewers and AI can use that context while relying on the diff, tests, CI, and ClawSweeper review as the source of truth for correctness and proof sufficiency.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/real-behavior-proof-policy.test.ts test/scripts/barnacle-auto-response.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts`\n  - 245 tests passed.\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check` across all changed OpenClaw files.\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --parallel-tests \"<focused tooling command>\"`\n  - Clean: no accepted or actionable findings.\n- ClawSweeper companion validation: `pnpm run check` passed.\n",
